Most people desire to take on federal government jobs after their graduation, so if you’re like this then this article on how to apply for federal government recruitment in Nigeria is a must-read for you. The first thing you’ll have to do is figure out what kind of job you want, your salary expectations, and which of the Government agencies, ministries, or parastatals you’re interested in. Next would be to find out which of them is recruiting, the available openings, and the eligibility requirements. Also, find out the different agency websites and keep tabs on them for when they’ll post job opportunities. The different federal government agencies will likely have specific eligibility requirements for each of their openings. However, outlined below are the general requirements you must possess to qualify for any of the jobs. It is important to note that the Federal Government does not recruit those with SSCE certificates only. You must possess either a B.SC, HND, OND, or NCE to get recruited into any of the Federal Government Agencies. Donate TEXT AD: Call Willie - +2348098788999 